Program: Omnibus
Title: Beyond the Ark
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jvj
Last Broadcast Date: 02 May 1990
A look at the conservation strategy of releasing animals bred in captivity back into the wild, the problems of doing so and why it is none the less important to do so as increasing numbers of species face extinction. Contributors include Dr Hilary O Box.